                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1161">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/862.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-12T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Before passing upon the additions suggested by your September 10, 6 p.m., the
                    Department desires to see the complete text and context of such additions, as it
                    feels that before assenting to any changes they should be submitted to the
                    President, who has approved the note sent you as it stands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
